## Suggested Learning Order

1. Build a simple Streamlit app with a file uploader.
2. Read and display text from an uploaded PDF.
3. Split the extracted text into chunks.
4. Generate embeddings for those chunks.
5. Store and search them using FAISS.
6. Connect an LLM to answer questions using the retrieved chunks.
7. Improve the UI and add advanced features.

This project mirrors the architecture used in many enterprise AI applications, so completing it will give you practical experience with concepts commonly used in GenAI interviews and real-world document assistant systems.
